  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: c7d67e59d4e1e1b4393f5ec76b762e5a, type: 3}
  m_Name: How To Play
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: 
  Title: How To Play
  Description: "You roll 5 dice at once and get scored based on what you rolled,
    each number on the dice is worth 100 times its value. The best roll you could
    get is having all the dice roll the same number, so try to get as many dice to
    roll the same number as you can! \n\nThankfully though, if you don't think your
    roll was as good as it could've been you can reroll up to 2 times\n\nBy clicking
    on the rolled dice or the dice in your egg carton you can slelect to keep them,
    choosing to keep dice will make it so if you choose to reroll your dice, the
    selected dice will stay, keeping the numbers they rolled, and the rest of the
    dice will be recycled to the cardboard box. Once the dice are recycled you can
    either add new dice to your egg carton to be rolled or, if you only have 5 dice,
    you can put the same dice back in your egg carton to roll again. \n\nSelectng
    all 5 dice will forfeit your rerolls and calculate your score based off the current
    roll. \n\nthere are many different catagories you can score points in and during
    scoring you get scored for all elegible catagories, but in case you're curious,
    I'll list all the catagories and how they're scored\n\nFirst, there's a catagory
    for each number on a die (ex. 1, 2, 3...), those catagories are scored by adding
    the number multiplied by how many times you rolled it (ex. four 3s = 1200$)\n\nThen,
    there are catagories baseds off of poker hands..."
